# Rust conventions for Dub

## Always

- Run `cargo fmt` after edits. The pre-commit hook does this; agents should mimic.
- Run `cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings` after non-trivial changes.
- Run `cargo nextest run -p <crate>` for the changed crate; full workspace before merge.
- Public items have `///` doc comments. `#![warn(missing_docs)]` is on in libraries.
- Use `thiserror` for library errors; `anyhow` for binaries / integration tests.
- No `unwrap()` outside test code. Use `?`, `.expect("why this can't fail: …")`, or proper error propagation.
- No `panic!` in library code outside `assert!` family in tests.

## Modules and naming

- Module names: `snake_case`, singular. Files: `transport.rs`, not `transports.rs`.
- Types: `PascalCase`. Acronyms get sentence case (`HttpClient`, not `HTTPClient`; `Rms`, not `RMS`).
- Constants: `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE`.
- Re-export key public types at the crate root via `pub use`.

## Errors

```rust
// Good — typed errors per crate
#[derive(Debug, thiserror::Error)]
pub enum LibraryError {
    #[error("library file not found: {path}")]
    NotFound { path: PathBuf },
    #[error("malformed entry at offset {offset}")]
    Malformed { offset: u64 },
}
```

## Comments

- No comments that narrate what the code does. `// Increment counter` adds nothing.
- Comments explain *why*: trade-offs, surprising invariants, references to PRD sections.
- Reference PRD sections by number when relevant: `// See PRD §6.1.1`.

## Tests

- TDD: write the failing test first.
- Property tests (`proptest`) for state machines and parsers.
- Golden tests (`insta`) for DSP regression.
- Tests live next to source as `#[cfg(test)] mod tests`.
- Integration tests in `tests/`.

## Things to avoid

- `unwrap()` outside tests
- `as` casts for numeric narrowing without comment
- `dyn Trait` heap allocation in hot paths
- `Mutex` / `RwLock` anywhere near the audio thread
- `unsafe` (we have `#![forbid(unsafe_code)]` at crate level; FFI crates exempt)
